          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
              "aonid": 26,
              "game-obj": "Actions",
              "name": "Recall Knowledge",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Uncommon",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 11,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "size"
          ],
          "edition": "legacy",
          "game-id": "36e474dd2f4c19b317214eccf55c8c77",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Medium",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0k?Pathfinder-Core-Rulebook",
                "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Core Rulebook",
              "page": 474,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "*Space:* 5 feet, *Reach (Tall):* 5 feet, *Reach (Long):* 5 feet",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 160,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "20f6f5f93a453f3006eb194c6d712042",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Undead",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Once living, these creatures were infused after death with void energy and soul-corrupting unholy magic. When reduced to 0 Hit Points, an undead creature is destroyed. Undead creatures are damaged by vitality energy and are healed by void energy, and don\u2019t benefit from healing vitality effects.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "6309897c89780f17449b984cbb6d26cb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "holy",
              "aonid": 517,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "holy",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Unholy",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the unholy trait are tied to powerful magical forces of cruelty and sin. They often have stronger effects on holy creatures. Creatures with this trait are strongly devoted to unholy causes, and often have weakness to holy. If a creature with weakness to unholy uses an unholy item or effect, it takes damage from its weakness.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
    "defense": {
      "ac": {
        "subtype": "armor_class",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "value": 17
      },
      "automatic_abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "harm",
              "aonid": 1552,
              "game-obj": "Spells",
              "name": "harm",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Final Blasphemy",
          "saving_throw": [
            {
              "dc": 18,
              "subtype": "save_dc",
              "text": "DC 18",
              "type": "stat_block_section"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "When the herexen is destroyed, it explodes in a wave of void energy with the effects of a 3-action *harm* spell (DC 18). The herexen is destroyed, so it doesn't gain any Hit Points from this use of harm, and it doesn't need to have any harm spells remaining to use this ability.",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 48,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "243cd4d729d5eddd1e2c4635b7985fb9",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Divine",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 455,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This magic comes from the divine tradition, drawing power from deities or similar sources. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to divine magic.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 118,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "3272a04f38d00c2316cbc6fe1eb1cda1",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "links": [
                {
                  "alt": "undead",
                  "aonid": 160,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "name": "undead",
                  "type": "link"
                }
              ],
              "name": "Void",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 463,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Effects with this trait heal undead creatures with void energy, deal void damage to living creatures, or manipulate void energy.  \n  \nPlanes with this trait are vast, empty reaches that suck the life from the living. They tend to be lonely, haunted planes, drained of color and filled with winds carrying the moans of the dead At the end of each round, a living creature takes at least minor void environmental damage. In the strongest areas of a void plane, they could take moderate or even major void damage at the end of each round. This damage has the death trait, and if a living creature is reduced to 0 Hit Points by this void damage and killed, it crumbles into ash and can become a wraith (see Monster Core).",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
      "hitpoints": [
        {
          "automatic_abilities": [
            {
              "ability_type": "automatic",
